The Nigerian Railway Corporation (NRC) has expressed regret over the failure of the locomotive train scheduled to convey passengers from Abuja-Kaduna. Mr Yakub Mahmood, NRC’s Deputy Director, Public Relations, said this in a statement made available to the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) on Wednesday in Abuja. “The management of the NRC expresses its regrets over the failure of the locomotive on the last train of Abuja-Kaduna Train Service of Tuesday, at the outer home signal of Rigassa station, Kaduna. “NRC hereby apologises for the inconvenience this incident may have caused all our esteemed passengers on board,’’ he said. Mahmood, however, announced that the uninterrupted train services between the Abuja-Kaduna route had since resumed accordingly. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.